commit 29ce39c2d7073ef27f998b3796346e7067a9fb48
Author: vchat-meme-blip <limeikenji@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Mar 28 17:44:27 2026 +0200

    fix(routing): use openclaw/default model ID for all local-llm HTTP requests
    
    Root cause of HTTP 404: the gateway's OpenAI-compat /v1/chat/completions
    endpoint is agent-centric — it only accepts "openclaw/default" (or similar
    "openclaw/<agentId>" format) as the model field, NOT raw provider IDs like
    "local-llm/model-id". Sending an unrecognised provider ID returns 404.
    
    Confirmed via official OpenClaw docs (docs.openclaw.ai/gateway/openai-http-api):
    "The model field MUST be openclaw/default — the gateway resolves this to the
    agent's configured model (agents.defaults.model.primary)."
    
    Fix applied to all four HTTP request sites:
    - sendMessageHttp() in gateway_service.dart — main chat path
    - sendVisionMessage() in gateway_service.dart — vision/image path (also adds
      missing Authorization header)
    - testInference() in local_llm_service.dart — diagnostic playground
    - analyseVideoFrames() in local_llm_service.dart — video analysis
    
    All now send: model="openclaw/default" + x-openclaw-model=<provider_id> header
    as an explicit routing hint. The gateway uses agents.defaults.model.primary
    (written by _patchOpenClawConfig() as "local-llm/<id>") for routing.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

