Author: vchat-meme-blip <limeikenji@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Mar 28 08:23:23 2026 +0200

    fix(routing): CRITICAL - local-llm via HTTP path, eliminate cloud fallback
    
    ROOT CAUSE: WS chat.send has no model parameter. It relies on the gateway's
    in-memory agents.defaults.model.primary config. If the openclaw reload after
    enabling local LLM didn't fully take effect (race condition), the gateway
    still routes to the cloud default -> 'API rate limit reached'.
    
    FIX 1 - Explicit model routing (gateway_service.dart):
      When selectedModel starts with 'local-llm/', sendMessage now forces the
      HTTP /v1/chat/completions path which passes the model ID explicitly in
      the request body. This bypasses the WS session's default routing entirely.
      Cloud models continue to use WS (agentic, stateful, tool support).
    
    FIX 2 - Strict health check (local_llm_service.dart):
      isServerHealthy no longer has a lenient config-only fallback. It now
      blocks until /v1/models endpoint confirms local-llm is actually loaded.
      Only exception: if token is unavailable (gateway regenerating), allows
      pass-through since the HTTP path sends model explicitly anyway.
    
    Also: reduced startup delays 800ms->300ms, 1000ms->500ms (1s saved).

