commit da8a69ec7b6dc5db8901fd336873e602fbc9dc2d
Author: vchat-meme-blip <limeikenji@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Mar 26 19:54:03 2026 +0200

    fix(llama): validate binary size in _isBinaryInstalled to bypass corrupt stub
    
    The previous broken download left a 9-byte GitHub 404 redirect at
    /root/.openclaw/bin/llama-server with chmod +x applied. The original
    `test -x` check only tests the permission bit, not whether the file is
    a real ELF binary. Result: _compileBinary() was never invoked because
    the 9-byte stub was treated as a valid installation, and _startServer()
    crashed the OS with "Process died immediately" every time.
    
    Add a size gate: binary must be > 1 MB (real llama-server is 5–15 MB).
    The corrupt stub (9 bytes) now fails the check, causing _compileBinary()
    to run the compile-from-source pipeline on next Start.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

