commit 6828308b83e9938c5dd630f27ece206dc20958f3
Author: vchat-meme-blip <limeikenji@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Mar 20 03:39:49 2026 +0200

    fix(local-llm): compile llama-server from source inside PRoot
    
    The previous implementation used a non-existent GitHub Releases URL
    (llama-server-android-arm64) which would 404 on first install.
    
    Fix: replaced _downloadBinary() with _compileBinary() which runs a
    PRoot shell script to build llama-server natively inside the Ubuntu
    layer:
      - apt-get install cmake make g++ git ca-certificates
      - git clone --depth 1 ggerganov/llama.cpp
      - cmake build --target llama-server -j4
      - install to /root/.openclaw/bin/llama-server
    
    This is the correct approach: Ubuntu ARM64 pre-built binaries are not
    consistently provided by the llama.cpp releases page (confirmed by a
    Feb 2026 GitHub issue). Compile-from-source inside PRoot guarantees
    glibc compatibility and correct ARM64 NEON instruction dispatch.
    
    The compile is a one-time setup. Once the binary exists at
    /root/.openclaw/bin/llama-server, subsequent app starts skip it.
    Estimated build time: 10-25 min on Snapdragon 8 Gen 1-3.
    
    Also fixed:
      - UI label: 'Installing binary' -> 'Compiling (10-25 min)'
      - 4 info-level lint hints (final field, activeThumbColor, curly braces,
        string interpolation brace)

